# Alfred State College to host 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships

Alfred State College will host the 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships on Feb. 19-22 at the Alfred State College Aquatic Center. The four-day event will feature 10 teams from across the SUNY system.

The Alfred State College Aquatic Center is a state-of-the-art facility that features a 10-lane, 25-yard competition pool with a separate diving well. The facility also features a 1,000-seat spectator area, a 1,500-square-foot strength and conditioning room, and a 1,000-square-foot multipurpose room.

The 10 teams competing in the championships are Alfred State, Brockport, Buffalo State, Cortland, Fredonia, Geneseo, New Paltz, Oneonta, Oswego, and Potsdam. The first event will begin at 10 a.m. on Wednesday, Feb. 19, with the preliminary rounds of the men’s and women’s 1,000-yard freestyle. The finals of the 1,000-yard freestyle will begin at 5 p.m. that evening.

The preliminary rounds of the 200-yard freestyle relay will begin at 10 a.m. on Thursday, Feb. 20, with the finals of the 200-yard freestyle relay, 500-yard freestyle, 200-yard individual medley, and 50-yard freestyle beginning at 5 p.m. that evening.

The preliminary rounds of the 400-yard individual medley, 100-yard butterfly, 200-yard freestyle, 100-yard breaststroke, and 100-yard backstroke will begin at 10 a.m. on Friday, Feb. 21, with the finals of those events beginning at 5 p.m. that evening.

The preliminary rounds of the 200-yard backstroke, 100-yard freestyle, 200-yard breaststroke, 200-yard butterfly, and 1,650-yard freestyle will begin at 10 a.m. on Saturday, Feb. 22, with the finals of those events, as well as the 400-yard freestyle relay, beginning at 5 p.m. that evening.

The awards ceremony will take place at approximately 8:30 p.m. on Saturday, Feb. 22.

Tickets for the event are $5 per session, $10 per day, or $30 for an all-session pass. Children under 12 will be admitted free of charge. Tickets will be available at the door.

For more information on the 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships, visit www.alfredstateathletics.com.

**Question:** What is the schedule for the 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships at Alfred State College?  

**Answer:**  
The 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships will take place from **February 19–22, 2014**, at the Alfred State College Aquatic Center. The schedule is as follows:  

- **Wednesday, Feb. 19**  
  - **10 a.m.**: Preliminary rounds of the men’s and women’s 1,000-yard freestyle.  
  - **5 p.m.**: Finals of the 1,000-yard freestyle.  

- **Thursday, Feb. 20**  
  - **10 a.m.**: Preliminary rounds of the 200-yard freestyle relay.  
  - **5 p.m.**: Finals of the 200-yard freestyle relay, 500-yard freestyle, 200-yard individual medley, and 50-yard freestyle.  

- **Friday, Feb. 21**  
  - **10 a.m.**: Preliminary rounds of the 400-yard individual medley, 100-yard butterfly, 200-yard freestyle, 100-yard breaststroke, and 100-yard backstroke.  
  - **5 p.m.**: Finals of the above events.  

- **Saturday, Feb. 22**  
  - **10 a.m.**: Preliminary rounds of the 200-yard backstroke, 100-yard freestyle, 200-yard breaststroke, 200-yard butterfly, and 1,650-yard freestyle.  
  - **5 p.m.**: Finals of the above events and the 400-yard freestyle relay.  
  - **8:30 p.m.**: Awards ceremony.  

**Tickets**: $5 per session, $10 per day, or $30 for an all-session pass (children under 12 admitted free). For more details, visit [www.alfredstateathletics.com](http://www.alfredstateathletics.com).  

**Facility**: The Alfred State College Aquatic Center features a 10-lane, 25-yard competition pool, a diving well, a 1,000-seat spectator area, and additional amenities like a strength and conditioning room.
